ange.\n\n**Impact**: Not quantifiable from trace data\n\n## Detailed Analysis\n\n<!-- reasoning-candidate tier=compute rank=1 -->\n#### Aligned GEMM shows matching Trace 1 and Trace 2 scoped kernel times\n\n**Identification:** The category contains one aligned GEMM surfaced for comparative review. **`aten::mm`** uses the **Tensile** vendor GEMM path. It was surfaced using aligned **GPU kernel time** totals and **`delta_us (trace2 - trace1)`** on the GEMM pairing; the delta is zero, so comparative kernel durations match. No operation is marked **`fusion_flagged: true`** in `gemm_metrics.json`. (source: `gemm_ops.csv` → `delta_us (trace2 - trace1)`, `lca_total_kernel_time_trace2_us`; `gemm_metrics.json` → `operations[].time_ms`, `operations[].library`, `operations[].efficiency.bound_type`, `impact_estimates`)\n\n**Data:**\n\n| Operation | Trace 1 Time (ms) | Trace 2 Time (ms) | Count (T1/T2) | Difference (ms) | FLOPS/Byte (T1) | Bound (T1) |\n|-----------|-------------------|-------------------|---------------|-----------------|-----------------|------------|\n| aten::mm | 0.200 | 0.200 | 1 / 1 | 0.000 | 170.67 | compute-bound |\n\nOn Trace 1, achieved throughput **~1.34 TFLOPS** is compared against **708 TFLOPS** from `operations[].efficiency.resolved_peak_maf` (`compute-bound` peak reference).\n\n**Reasoning for Slowdown:** Trace 2 is not comparatively slower here in terms of GEMM GPU kernel time. Aligned comparative kernel durations match Trace 1 for this shape and invocation count.\n\n**Resolution:** Comparative findings prioritize differences between traces. With **no** measurable scoped kernel-duration gap on this row, GEMM comparative optimization adds little for this pairing. Broader throughput gains would require workloads or fused patterns to diverge versus this parity pairing, which is outside what this differential slice targets.\n\n**Impact estimate:**\n\nImpact estimate is not quantifiable from trace data.\n","isEmpty":false,"exceededLimit":false,"totalL