{"type":"tool_call","subtype":"completed","call_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XMhoPdNGAm8osDCXqFxHaw","tool_call":{"readToolCall":{"args":{"path":"/home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens/evals/unit_tests_comparative/test02_attention_both_unfused/analysis_output_ref/category_findings/gemm_findings.md"},"result":{"success":{"content":"<!--\nCopyright (c) 2024 - 2025 Advanced Micro Devices, Inc. All rights reserved.\n\nSee LICENSE for license information.\n-->\n\n# GEMM — comparative findings\n\n**Status:** SUCCESS  \n**Platform:** MI300X (Trace 1 peak references: `efficiency.resolved_peak_maf` for compute-bound, `efficiency.resolved_peak_hbm_bw` for memory-bound).  \n**Scope:** All times are **GPU kernel time** (Trace 1 in metrics; Trace 2 from aligned CSV). Category GPU kernel time on Trace 1: **0.18 ms** (**100%** of GEMM category per `gemm_metrics.json`).\n\n## Overview\n\nGEMM work on Trace 1 is a single aligned **memory-bound** BF16 **`aten::bmm`** (batch \\(B{=}8\\), shapes `(8,512,64)` × `(8,64,512)`). On Trace 1 the op achieves about **0.28 TB/s** versus **5.3 TB/s** peak HBM bandwidth (`efficiency.resolved_peak_hbm_bw` for **memory-bound** `efficiency.bound_type`). In **comparative** mode, paired rows use **Trace 2 GPU kernel time** well **below** Trace 1 for the same counts, so Trace 1 is the slower trace on this GEMM and warrants tuning or workload changes. No operation has **`fusion_flagged: true`** in `gemm_metrics.json`.\n\n## Operations breakdown (Trace 1 vs Trace 2)\n\n| Operation | Trace 1 Time (ms) | Trace 2 Time (ms) | Count (T1/T2) | Difference (ms) | FLOPS/Byte (T1) | Bound (T1) |\n|-----------|-------------------|-------------------|---------------|-----------------|-----------------|------------|\n| aten::bmm | 0.18 | 0.08 | 2 / 2 | -0.10 | 51.2 | memory-bound |\n\nTrace 2 time and difference from `category_data/gemm_ops.csv` → `lca_total_kernel_time_trace2_us`, `delta_us (trace2 - trace1)`. Count T2 from `lca_kernel_count_trace2`.\n\n## Key observations (Trace 1)\n\n- **Comparative:** Aligned Trace 1 GPU kernel totals are **180 µs** versus **80 µs** on Trace 2 for the same invocation pattern, so Trace 1 spends about **0.10 ms** more GPU kernel time on this batched matmul than the Trace 2 pairing.\n- **Hardware headroom (Trace 1):** Achieved **~0.28 TB/s** sits far below the **5.3 TB/s** memory-bandwidth peak on the bound-type axis, so vendor GEMM tuning or improved memory access behavior on Trace 1 could shrink time even before matching Trace 2.\n\n---\n\n## Impact Summary\n\n| Recommendation | Type | Estimated Savings (ms) | Estimated Improvement (E2E %) | Confidence |\n|----------------|------|------------------------|-------------------------------|------------|\n| Close Trace 1 vs Trace 2 GEMM kernel-time gap (`aten::bmm`) | kernel_tuning | 0.075–0.10 | 26.79–35.72 | medium |\n\n*From `gemm_metrics.json` → `impact_estimates` (aligned with reasoning candidate below).*\n\n---\n\n## Recommendations\n\n### P1: Trace 1 attention BMM slower than Trace 2 pairing\n**Insight**: Trace 1 accumulates **0.18 ms** of GPU kernel time on **`aten::bmm`** versus **0.08 ms** on Trace 2 for the same **2 / 2** invocations and BF16 batch matmul shapes, so Trace 1 is clearly slower on this aligned GEMM slice.\n\n**Action**: On the algorithmic side, keep batched matmuls (e.g. `torch.bmm`) instead of many tiny separate GEMMs and consider whether fused attention or reduced intermediate traffic helps this memory-bound path. On the kernel side, pursue vendor GEMM paths and tuning that raise effective HBM bandwidth toward the **5.3 TB/s** peak for these shapes, and profile with hardware counters if efficiency stays low after tuning.\n\n**Impact**: ~0.075–0.10 ms savings (26.79–35.72% of E2E)\n\n## Detailed Analysis\n\n<!-- reasoning-candidate tier=compute rank=1 -->\n#### Trace 1 BF16 batched attention matmul uses more GPU kernel time than Trace 2\n\n**Identification:** The row was flagged from aligned **GPU kernel time**: Trace 1 totals exceed Trace 2 for the same op name, shapes, and invocation counts on the comparative pairing. The op is **memory-bound** on Trace 1. No **`fusion_flagged: true`** appears in `gemm_metrics.json` for this category. (source: `gemm_metrics.json` → `operations[].time_ms`, `operations[].efficiency.bound_type`, `operations[].efficiency.resolved_peak_hbm_bw`, `gemm_ops.csv` → `lca_total_kernel_time_trace1_us`, `lca_total_kernel_time_trace2_us`, `delta_us (trace2 - trace1)`)\n\n**Data:**\n\n| Operation | Trace 1 Time (ms) | Trace 2 Time (ms) | Count (T1/T2) | Difference (ms) | FLOPS/Byte (T1) | Bound (T1) |\n|-----------|-------------------|-------------------|---------------|-----------------|-----------------|------------|\n| aten::bmm | 0.18 | 0.08 | 2 / 2 | -0.10 | 51.2 | memory-bound |\n\nOn Trace 1, achieved **~0.28 TB/s** is compared with **5.3 TB/s** from `operations[].efficiency.resolved_peak_hbm_bw` (**memory-bound** peak reference).\n\n**Reasoning for Slowdown:** Trace 1 spends substantially more GPU kernel time than Trace 2 on the same batched BF16 matrix multiply work. Trace 2 finishes the paired invocations in roughly half the GPU kernel time Trace 1 requires, leaving a clear comparative gap to close on Trace 1.\n\n**Resolution:** Improving Trace 1 requires both reducing redundant memory traffic where the model allows and using better-tuned or better-selected vendor GEMM kernels for this memory-bound case. With **~51 FLOPs/byte** on Trace 1, sustained time is dominated by moving operand and result bytes through HBM; kernels that move those bytes faster therefore finish each invocation sooner without changing the math.\n\n**Impact estimate:**\n\n- Low end (75% gap target): 0.075 ms savings (26.79% E2E)\n- High end (100% gap target): 0.10 ms savings (35.72% E2E)\n- Range: 0.075–0.10 ms (26.79–35.72% E2E)\n","isEmpty":false,"exceededLimit":false,"totalLines":75,"fileSize":5464,"path":"/home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens/evals/unit_tests_comparative/test02_attention_both_unfused/analysis_output_ref/category_findings/gemm_findings.md","readRange":{"startLine":1,"endLine":75},"relatedCursorRulePaths":[],"relatedCursorRules":[]}}}},"model_call_id":"de66684d-d902-43fc-a184-f6f237127dea-54-ngqy","session_id":"254aeb55-f6f0-4bd2-bb42-0a4a9aed7e22","timestamp_ms":1777504762810}
