race 2 is faster.\n\n## Key findings\n\n1. **Trace 1 softmax dominates this category and a large share of total GPU time** while Trace 2 executes the matched softmax roughly **2.75×** faster in kernel time (110 µs vs 40 µs).\n2. **Possible miscategorization:** `aten::softmax` is softmax / stable-normalize semantics; it may be more usefully grouped with reduction- or normalization-style categories for future filter tuning (not a measurement error).\n\n## Recommendations\n\n### P1: Close Trace 1 vs Trace 2 softmax kernel-time gap\n**Insight**: Trace 1 spends substantially more GPU kernel time on the matched `aten::softmax` than Trace 2, and this one op accounts for most of Trace 1 GPU time in the trace.\n**Action**: Diff the two runs (PyTorch / GPU library versions, attention fusion, inductor vs eager, and dispatch for `softmax_warp_forward`) and align Trace 1 with the faster Trace 2 configuration or kernel selection; profile Trace 1 softmax if versions already match.\n**Impact**: Not quantifiable from trace data\n\n## Detailed Analysis\n\n<!-- reasoning-candidate tier=compute rank=1 -->\n#### Trace 1 softmax slower than Trace 2 under matched LCA\n\n**Identification:** The only row in this category is `aten::softmax` with high Trace 1 share of overall GPU time, while paired Trace 2 LCA kernel time is much smaller `(source: \\`category_data/other_metrics.json\\` → \\`operations[]\\`, \\`category_data/other_ops.csv\\` → \\`lca_total_kernel_time_trace1_us\\`, \\`lca_total_kernel_time_trace2_us\\`, \\`delta_us (trace2 - trace1)\\`)`.\n\n**Data:**\n\n| Operation | Args | Trace 1 Time (ms) | Trace 2 Time (ms) | Count (T1/T2) | Difference (ms) | FLOPS/Byte (T1) | Bound (T1) | Sub-Category |\n|-----------|------|-------------------|-------------------|---------------|-----------------|-----------------|------------|--------------|\n| aten::softmax | (8,512,512) bf16 | 0.11 | 0.04 | 1 / 1 | -0.07 | — | — | miscellaneous |\n\nKernel detail on Trace 1: `softmax_warp_forward<float, float, float, 4, true>` `(source: \\`category_data/other_ops.csv\\` → \\`trunc_kernel_details\\`)`.\n\n**Reasoning for Slowdown:** Trace 1 takes about **2.75×** longer than Trace 2 for the softmax kernel under the same LCA name, a **0.07 ms** absolute gap on Trace 1. That is a straight pairwise comparison of GPU kernel duration, not a roofline shortfall. There is no signal here that Trace 2 is anomalously slow relative to Trace 1.\n\n**Resolution:** Reconciling framework, compiler, and library paths between the two traces addresses the gap directly: a different `aten::softmax` implementation, fusion with surrounding attention math, or inductor-generated code on one side can change which warp-level softmax kernel is chosen and how much work remains fused, without any change to tensor shapes shown in the trace.\n\n**Impact estimate:** Impact estimate is not quantifiable from trace data.\n","isEmpty":false,"exceededLimit":false,"totalLines":53,"fileSize":4540,"path":"/home/AMD/khoffmey/dev/TraceLens/evals/unit_tests_comparative/test02_attention_both_unfused/analysis_output_ref/category_findings/other_findings.md","readRange":{"startLine":1,"endLine":53},"relatedCursorRulePaths":[],"relatedCursorRules":[]}}}},"model_call_id":"de66684d-d902-43fc-a184-f6f237127dea-54-ngqy","session_id":"254aeb55-f6f0-4bd2-bb42-0a4a9aed7e22","timestamp_ms":1777504763319}
